body:
@w4nderlust thanks for the advice, I agree that this feature should be generally available for different inputs/outputs. However, considering how most data augmentation techniques are highly domain-specific (image, text, timeseries, etc), I was wondering if we should initially approach this feature as being configurable depending on the input data type (text, image, numerical, timeseries, etc)?   

Some brief [literature review](https://arxiv.org/pdf/1702.05538.pdf) indicates that some domain-agnostic techniques exist, but I am not sure of their accuracy/performance/general acceptance within the ML community. 

Any advice would be much appreciated, thanks!

@andife unfortunately no updates. There will soon be updates on using pretrained image encoders and having more architectures available though.
This is still a feature we want to add, but has not been prioritized yet.
Still very open for community contributions about it!
